WHY DO WE COLLECT THIS DATA FROM YOU?
The personal information we collect varies according to user, transaction, and purpose, but our primary purpose is the efficient and satisfactory conduct of our business and for related legal purposes. Please not that you are responsible for any third-party personal data obtained, published, or shared through our Platform by you.
We use your personal data for the following purposes:
Usage and Collection
Purpose
To allow you to create a Profile with us, use our Services and enter any of our draws, claim any prizes and have such prizes awarded to you.
Contractual necessity: to the extent the information we collect for these purposes is necessary to fulfil our contract with you; and our third-party partner’s legitimate interests, to the extent the information is necessary to allow our third-party partners to fulfil its contract with you and ensure their terms of use are complied with.
To communicate with you about your Profile and your use of our Services, such as your entry in Competitions and to effectively manage your Profile.
Contractual necessity, to the extent that the information is necessary to fulfil our contract with you (for example, to inform you about how you can claim your prize); our legitimate interests, to the extent the information is necessary to process queries you make in relation to your Profile and account and to effectively manage our relationship with you as our user and your Profile to effectively manage your Profile.
If you communicate with us (for example, if you email or call us), we will use your information for dealing with your queries, training, and customer service purposes.
Contractual necessity: where you provide information that is necessary for us to ful fil our contract with you and provide our Services. Our legitimate interests are to handle your queries and provide you with the requested information, ensure high customer service quality and to train staff in responding to such requests.
To carry out identity and credit reference checks, to verify the bank account information you provide to us and to establish your eligibility to use our Services, in accordance with our Terms of Service and Competition Terms.
Our legitimate interest is to the integrity of our Services and business operations and to ensure that our users are able to comply with our terms and do not misuse our Services. Legal requirements, to the extent we are required by law to verify any of your information in order to provide our Services to you.
To administer and effectively manage our Competitions, including selecting winners and disqualifying entries.
Our legitimate interests to ensure the effective management of our operations and the integrity of our Services.
To publish your information on our “winners” page of our website and app, when you win in any of our Competitions. This information includes your name, home city, and photograph.
To publish your information on our “winners” page of our website and app, when you win in any of our Competitions. This information includes your name, home city and photograph. We rely on our legitimate interests to publish this information.
To send you marketing communications about our Services (and the products or services of third parties that we make available through our Services), or to send you our newsletter when you sign up to receive this and to monitor whether you open our emails and/or click on URLs in our emails.
We rely on your consent, where this is required by law. Otherwise, werely on our legitimate interest to keep you informed of products and services on our platforms, when we are allowed by law to do so.
To carry out market research and create marketing profiles about our users and understand their preferences in relation to our Services (including the products and services available through these).Publishing information on our “winners” page.
Our legitimate interest to carry out marketing activities.
To display our advertisements to you on other platforms, such as social media platforms or to display on our website and app advertisements which we think you might like.
Your consent, where we obtain this information by using cookies or where otherwise required by law. Otherwise, we rely on our and third parties’ legitimate interests to carry out marketing activities and inform you of products and services we think you might like.
To compile statistics and analysis about the use of our Services and use such statistics to enable us to provide a better service, features, and functionality to you and other users. Your consent, where we obtain this information by using cookies.
Our legitimate interests (where consent is not required by law) so as to ensure the smooth and effective functioning of our Services, to make sound business decisions about our products and services and to design, inform and deploy our business strategies.
To protect the security of our Services, information systems and assets, to monitor compliance with our Terms of Service and Competition Terms, to prevent fraud and other prohibited or illegal activities in relation to our Services.
Our legitimate interests to protect our business assets against fraud, misuse, and illegal activities or security threats.
To respond to legitimate requests for the disclosure of information, made by public authorities, law enforcement or government bodies or under a court order.
Legal requirement, to the extent we are obliged under law to process such requests. Our legitimate interests to assist legitimate investigations carried out by official authorities.
To respond to complaints, to protect our legal rights and to establish, exercise or defend legal claims relating to our platforms and/or our products and services.
Our legitimate interests to protect our legal rights.
For tax, accounting, record keeping and audit purposes. Legal requirements, to the extent the law requires that we use your information (for example, to comply with our tax obligations).
Our legitimate interest to effectively manage our business, audit our business processes and make informed business decisions.
HOW DO WE COLLECT YOUR DATA?
This section explains generally the sources from which, and how we collect and process personal data.
i) During profile registration:
We collect Personal Data from you when you use certain services on our Platform including when you sign up for an account, create or share, and message or communicate. This can include information on or about the services you provide or about how you use our Services. Personal Data and other details about you that you supply as part of the registration process or that are collected by us when you use the Services are used to provide you with the Services and information as set out in our Terms of Service. We will not use that information for any purpose other than the Services.
ii) When you communicate with us:
If you contact us in relation to any of the Services (via email, telephone, post or otherwise), we may collect and retain your contact details and your communication for the purpose of handling your query and keeping records of communications. When your communications with us provide us with certain technical information, such as internet protocol (IP) address, browser type, time zone setting, location, device operating system, and other technologies that may be utilised for you to access our Platform or communicate with us otherwise.
iii) When you submit any personal information:
When you submit your personal information to us voluntarily for any purposes, we may retain such information and process it. This information may include details such as (name, age, gender, identity card number, passport number, date of birth, education, race, ethnic origin, nationality, citizenship, biometric information), contact details such as (address, email, phone numbers), family information such as (marital status, name of spouse or child or immediate family), occupation details, bank details such as (bank account number(s), card details) and other information. In addition, we may from time-to-time request for certain other personal information that may be relevant for us to consider your request for any other products, services or features made available on our Platform. Failure to supply such data may result in us being unable to open, establish, continue and/or provide Account, products, services or features in relation to guidelines issued by authorities.
iv) When you visit our Platform:
When you visit our Platform, we may collect your location data, GPS related and other relative information from the internet browser you are using.
v) When you link your payment institution:
When you link your payment institution to your profile on our Platform, we may collect information from your bank, any partner institution, crypto wallet and/or from any provider issuing and managing the distribution of e-money to you. This is required for us to provide our Services.
vi) When you link/interact with any social media account:
We may collect information related to your social media account once you connect it to our Platform and/or when you interact with us or our content through any social media features (e.g., the “Like” buttons) integrated on our Platform.
vii) When fraud prevention agencies and/or other third parties carry out identification checks:
We may also verify and source personal information/data about you from third party sources, (both public and private) such as your employers, regulatory or other authorities, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) as well as from the public domain.
HOW WILL WE USE YOUR DATA?
We use the personal data we collect or receive from our Users for the purposes described in this Policy and for other business purposes allowed by law, including the development, delivery, and performance of our services, and sharing of such data with our affiliates for business related purposes, and as follows:
• To provide and maintain our Service.
• To manage your Account registration and usage.
• For the development, compliance and undertaking of the contract for the Services or of any other contract with us through the Service.
• To contact you by email, telephone calls, SMS, or other equivalent forms of electronic communication.
• To attend and manage your requests to us.
• To resolve disputes, investigate and address your concerns, and monitor and improve our responses.
• To help maintain the safety, security, and integrity of our Platform, databases, and technology assets and to detect and prevent transactional fraud.
• For testing, research, analysis, and a product and service development.
• For facilitating and processing your transactions with us and with our third party affiliates and business partners.
• To respond to law enforcement requests and as required by applicable laws, court orders, or governmental regulations.
• For fraud or crime prevention and investigation, transaction disputes, data analytics, audit and debt collection and in order that services may be processed by us.
• Conducting any action to meet our obligations to comply with Anti Money Laundering and Counter Terrorism Financing (“AML-CFT”) regulations and/or international guidance or regulatory requests relating to or in connection with the detection, investigation and prevention of money laundering, terrorist financing, bribery, corruption, tax evasion, fraud, criminal and/or unlawful activities, evasion of economic or trade sanctions and/or any acts or attempts to circumvent or violate any laws relating to these matters.
• For investigations or enquiries as to whether or not any user is a sanctioned person, or otherwise related to and/or associated with a sanctioned entity in any way; and for reporting or taking any remedial or preventive action in relation thereto.
• For our internal record keeping and/or any activity related or incidental to any above mentioned purposes.
• For other purposes such as data analysis, identifying usage trends, determining the effectiveness of our promotional campaigns, to evaluate and improve our service, marketing and your experience with us etc.
We have carried out balancing tests for all the data processing we carry out on the basis of our legitimate interests, as described hereinabove. You can obtain information on any of our balancing tests by contacting us using the details set out in the “Contact Us” section below.
Wherever we rely on your consent related to your data, you will always be able to withdraw such consent at any time. Please note that we may have other legal grounds for processing your data for other purposes including those set out hereinabove. You have the right to opt-out of direct marketing or profiling we carry out for direct marketing purposes at any time. You can do this by (i) clicking on the unsubscribe link in the relevant marketing communication, (ii) changing your marketing preferences through your Profile, or (iii) emailing us using the contact details given hereinabove. We do not use your personal data to make automated decisions about you which have a legal or similarly significant effect upon you. We have carried out balancing tests for all the data processing we carry out on the basis of our legitimate interests, as described hereinabove. You can obtain information on any of our balancing tests by contacting us using the details set out in the “Contact Us” section below.
METHODS OF DATA PROCESSING
We, at Klink Finance Limited, take appropriate security measures to prevent unauthorised access, disclosure, modification, or any unauthorised destruction of your data. The data processing is carried out using computers and/or IT enabled tools that follow organisational procedures and methods which are strictly in adherence to the purposes indicated in this Policy. In addition to us, the data may be accessible to certain types of persons in charge, involved with the operation of this Platform (administration, sales, marketing, legal, system administration) or external parties appointed by us (such as third-party technical service providers, mail carriers, payment providers, host servers), if necessary. The updated list of these parties may be requested from us at any time.
TRANSFER AND SHARING OF DATA
Depending on your location, your data may be transferred to a server in a country other than where you are resided, for storage or processing. If any such transfer takes place, you can find out more by checking the relevant sections of this Policy or inquire from us using the information provided in the contact section. We may store, process, and/or transfer personal data to countries outside of the European Economic Area or EEA, including countries where the European Commission has not made a decision of an adequate level of protection of personal data, but in these cases we will ask for your consent regarding such a data transfer.
We may share your personal data with following recipients:
• Internal recipients –
We may disclose your data to authorised employees who require such access in order to fulfil their role with us. Our employees are specifically trained with regards to the sensitivity, handling and protection of your data and its privacy.
• Judicial, administrative and other public authorities –
We may share or disclose your data if required to do so by the law, by a request from a competent authority or regulator, to comply with a court order, to obtain legal remedies or defend our Platform’s rights, to contribute with investigations related to fraud, identity theft etc. We may also share your data with fraud prevention agencies: we share and confirm information with these parties so as to confirm that you are eligible to use our Services and prevent fraudulent activity through our Services.
• Service providers –
We may share your data with third-party service providers who may process it on our behalf for the purposes identified in this Policy. These parties shall use your information on our instructions and only to the extent of providing us with their services. In particular, we may use third-party providers for website hosting, maintenance, payment provider services, mail carriers, customer support, marketing services, identity checking etc.
• Banks and payment institutions –
We may share your data with the banks and/or other payment institutions and providers issuing and managing the distribution of e-money to you including any crypto exchange etc., which you link to your profile for the purposes of payment or transfer.
• Social media networks and advertisers –
We may share your data with social media networks, subject to your marketing preferences, such as Facebook, Twitter and other advertisers in order to present our advertisements to you on these platforms. This may include sharing with these social networks any actions that you take on our Platform, such as your visits and your interactions on our website, information collected from cookies or similar technologies. This allows us to measure the effectiveness of our advertising, improve our marketing practices, and helps us deliver more relevant advertising to you and people like you. Further information on how these social media networks enable you to exercise your data protection rights, and subsequently processes your information can be found in their respective Privacy Policy available on their websites.
• Business advisers -
We may share your data with our legal advisers, accountants, business consultants, insurers and other business advisers, to the extent as is necessary for them to provide us with their services.
• In the event that our business is sold or integrated with another business –
We may share your data with our advisers and/or any prospective purchaser’s adviser and such data shall be passed to the new owners of the business/our legal successors.
Please note that we publicly disclose the identity of the winners of our sweepstakes, unless you specifically ask us not to do so.
RETENTION TIME
We will store your data for as long as it is required for us to fulfil the purposes for which we have collected it, as described in this Policy, and for such further period as is necessary to comply with our legal and regulatory obligations, to exercise our legal rights and to protect our business from legal claims ancillary thereto. Therefore:
• Personal Data collected for purposes related to the performance of a contract between us shall be retained until such contract has been fully performed.
• Personal Data collected for the purposes of the our legitimate interests shall be retained as long as needed to fulfil such interests. You may find specific information regarding the legitimate interests pursued by the us within the relevant sections of this Policy or by contacting us.
We may retain your data for a period longer than mentioned hereinabove, after seeking your consent to such prolonged retention up until you withdraw your consent. Once the retention period expires, your data will be deleted. Therefore, the right of access, the right to erasure, the right to rectification and the right to data portability cannot be enforced after expiration of the retention period.
YOUR RIGHTS RELATED TO YOUR DATA
You have the right to exercise any or all the following rights in relation to your data shared, stored, processed and/or retained by us:
• Withdraw consent at any time:
You have the right to withdraw your consent to the processing of your data at any time.
• Object to processing of your data:
You have the right to object to the processing of your data even if the processing is being carried out for legal reasons other than those based on your consent. Further details are provided in the dedicated section in this Policy.
• Access Data:
You have the right to learn how your data is being processed by us and obtain disclosure regarding certain aspects of the processing.
• Verify and seek rectification:
You have the right to verify the accuracy of your data and ask for it to be updated or corrected.
• Restrict the processing of your data:
You have the right, under certain circumstances, to restrict the processing of your data. In such a case, we will not process your data for any purpose other than storing it.
• Deletion or removal of your data:
You have the right, under certain circumstances, to request the erasure or removal of your data from our Platform.
• Request details or transfer of your data:
You have the right to request the details of your data in a structured and machine-readable format and, if technically feasible, to have it transmitted to another controller without any hindrance. This provision is applicable provided that the data is processed through automation and that the processing is based on your consent, on a contract which you are a party to or on any pre-contractual obligations thereof.
• Lodge a complaint:
If you have any unresolved concern, you have the right to complain to the data protection authority. However, we will appreciate it if you address your issues with us first before approaching the relevant authorities, and we will try our best to resolve your issues. Any requests regarding your user rights can be made to by writing to us directly at our e-mail provided hereinabove. These requests can be made free of charge and will be addressed by us as early as possible. If any of these issues further persist, you can send a request to the relevant data protection authority.
